Table

Tables are used to organize and display data efficiently. It renders a <table> element by default.

Import#

import {
  Table,
  Thead,
  Tbody,
  Tfoot,
  Tr,
  Th,
  Td,
  TableCaption,
} from "@chakra-ui/react"

Table Variants#

The table component comes in 3 variants: simple, striped, and unstyled. The default variant is simple

Change the variant values to see the other variants.

  },
  {
    name: "Lucas Harper",
    company: "Stone Tech Zone",

    number: "FRB1235476",
  },
  {
    name: "Ethan James",
    company: "Fiber Notion",
    email: "ethan@fiber.com",
    number: "FRB1235476",
  },
]
;<Flex direction="column">
  {billingData.map((row) => {
    return (
      <BillingRow
        name={row.name}
        company={row.company}
        email={row.email}
        number={row.number}
      />
    )
  })}
</Flex>

colorScheme

Type

Default
"gray"

Type
"sm" | "md" | "lg"
Default
"md"

variant

Type
"unstyled" | "simple" | "striped"
Default
"simple"

Description

Type
boolean

isNumeric

Description

Type
boolean

Description

Type
"bottom" | "top"
Default
"bottom"
